document_data.mainbody:
Farnath Ilistar II was the fifth King of the Ilistar Dynasty who ruled the city-state of Westgate.
Farnath II reclaimed the throne of Westgate for his family when the cambion King Iyachtu Xvim was forced to flee the city by a mercenary host in the . He ruled until the .
Farnath II was the great-great-grandson of King Farnath I. He was descended from King Belhendars younger half-brother. His son and heir was the simpleton Prince Farnath III and his younger brother was Temprith.
